upgradeInstructions:
Thanks for upgrading! In order to improve the performance of this content pack all incoming events now need to be tagged with "tenant=nxos". The easiest way to do this is leverage the multi-VIP + tag option available in Log Insight 3.3 and newer. Directions are provided below.

IMPORTANT: If you do not make these changes, the content pack will no longer work.

A. Multi-VIP Setup

On the Log Insight server, configure a VIP to filter Nexus logs and append the appropriate context keyword.
  • Navigate to Administration -> Cluster.
  • Select “New Virtual IP Address.”
  • Enter the desired IP address (located on the same subnet as the Log Insight service) and FQDN.
  • Add the tag “product=nxos” to the virtual IP address.
IMPORTANT: Add the FQDN to DNS.

B. Nexus Syslog Configuration
  • config t
  • logging server host [severity-level [use-vrf vrf-name]]
  • logging source-interface loopback virtual-interface
  • show logging server
  • copy running-config startup-config
IMPORTANT: host should be the FQDN configured in part A above.
name: Cisco - Nexus
author: VMware, Inc.

IMPORTANT: To fully leverage the power of this content pack Hitachi Compute blade is required. In addition, the Hitachi Compute Blade Management Module (SVP)must be configured and enable syslog setting.

This content pack enables:

Proactive monitoring of your Hitachi Compute Blade Environment

• Quickly identify issues: The Overview dashboard gives you a single pane of glass to find problems in your Hitachi Compute Blade environment while the Powerdashboard does the same to isolate Server power related issues.
• Drill down to determine the root cause: Dashboard filters make it easy to see logs from specific parts of your Hitachi Compute Blade environment.
• Easily consume data: Powerful and dynamic visualizations make it possible to detect anomalies, perform trending analysis, and pinpoint specific issues through targeted queries.
• Alerts: Know what to monitor in your Hitachi Compute Blade Management Module audit logs and get notified when such events are detected.

Track changes and isolate security threats

• Configuration management: Track user-initiated changes and automated Hitachi Compute Blade actions through the Configuration dashboard.
• Environmental changes: Get a complete picture from the Server - Maintenance dashboard or see more specific information like what compute blade are having issue with power through Power.
• Security: The Security dashboard allows you to find who is logging into Hitachi Compute Blade Management Module devices from which locations and through what means.

Additional information and context

• Query notes: Each dashboard widget includes information about the widget and any other information making it possible to understand the data presented.
• Inventory: The Overview dashboard quantifies results seen through Hitachi Compute Blade Management Module audit logs making it simple to ensure complete environment monitoring.

info:
The content pack for Microsoft® IIS® provides you with information about key entities of any IIS installation’s health using Log Insight’s ability to collect events from one or more log files.

Log Insight offers very intuitive graphical representation, especially with regards to log events. Spikes in the number and types of messages received can be flagged as events with external notifications. System administrators can drill into these events for looking at where and why these are being generated.

The Microsoft® IIS® Content pack includes 4 dashboards with a total of 27 widgets and 6 alarms. The content pack enables the user to monitor the IIS server in an easily readable graphical form. It provides:

• Overview of IIS server: This includes monitoring the count of all events and error events over time. It also gives you information about the source (client IP) from where the request originates and the destination (server IP) which serves it along with average response time of the IIS server.

• General Information: User can view the number of requests successfully served by the server along with any URL redirection info. Also gives information about the number of hits from a user along with the number of anonymous hits to your IIS server.

• Error Monitoring: This includes monitoring various client and server errors encountered on your IIS server.
name: Microsoft - IIS
author: VMware, Inc.

info:

Log Insight offers very intuitive graphical representation, especially with regards to log events. Spikes in the number and types of messages received can be flagged as events with external notifications. The Microsoft® Sharepoint® Content pack includes six dashboards with a total of 29 widgets and 6 alarms. The content pack enables the user to monitor the Sharepoint server in an easily readable graphical form. It provides:

• General Overview of SharePoint Server: This includes monitoring the count of various events over time or to categorize the usage of various processes/products and the various categories under those areas. Also gives an idea of various events based on the severity levels as seen in the SharePoint ULS logs.

• General Exceptions: The widgets under this dashboard enable the user to monitor various security, authentication and SP foundation related exceptions.

• Error Analysis: Errors in SharePoint logs are categorized under various severity levels such as critical, unexpected etc.
This dashboard along with 4 widgets groups the various errors based on the area, category, and process they fall under. It also includes a query widget which discusses about correlation id and events requiring administrative intervention.

• Usage Data information: This is the data about usage on SharePoint Farm, like Page requests, feature use etc. The content pack gives you usage information about feature usage, site inventory usage and page request usage by querying the various views available in the SharePoint database.

 Note: For SharePoint 2013 there would be no data seen for the dashboard Site Inventory Usage as the default view SiteInventory is not present in the database.
name: Microsoft - SharePoint
author: VMware, Inc.

info:
The content pack for Microsoft® SQL Server® provides you with information about key entities of any Microsoft® SQL Server® installation’s health using Log Insight’s ability to collect events from one or more log files.

• Server related errors and invalid queries: MS SQL server can encounter various media failure and database engine software related errors. Here you can monitor the various server related issues and raise an alarm to rectify it. Along with this you can also see errors related to insufficient resources, and invalid queries.

info:
Overview
 
The Content Pack for Oracle® Databases tailors VMware vRealize Log Insight capabilities to monitor Oracle Database Alert and Listener Logs. VMware vRealize Log Insight delivers real-time log management for VMware environments, with machine learning-based Intelligent Grouping, high performance search and better troubleshooting across physical, virtual, and cloud environments. 
 
With the Content Pack for Oracle Databases, you can apply powerful analytic-based technology to identify and solve database specific problems. The unstructured data collection capabilities of VMware vRealize Log Insight means reduced setup time and proactive management capabilities that adapt to your changing environment. 
 
Quickly expose internal database errors to your team and Oracle Support Services through real time analysis of the Oracle Database Alert and Listener Log files. The friendly interface is designed to eliminate time lost navigating log files on the command line. By leveraging the VMware vRealize Log Insight platform, the Content Pack for Oracle Databases provides accessible log management for every member of your team, and all teams in your organization. 
 
Highlights
 - Accurate monitoring of your Oracle Database installation
 - Key Oracle Database log files are covered—Alert, Listener
 
Description
The content pack for Oracle Database provides you with information about key events of a database installation’s health using vRealize Log Insight’s ability to monitor Oracle Database Logs. The content pack enables:
 
Accurate monitoring of your Oracle Database installation
Focus on known problems through monitoring events written to log files.
 
Key Oracle Database log files are covered—Alert, Listener
Six dashboards containing more than 20 widgets are included from alert and listener that go in depth to quantify your data in a multitude of manners to help diagnose problems in your Oracle database installation.
 
Minimum requirements
VMware vRealize Log Insight 2.5
Oracle Database server running one of the following versions on Linux or Windows:
 - Oracle Database 11g
 - Oracle Database 12c
 
Setup and configuration
 
1. Installation
 
To install the Oracle - Database content pack for VMWare vRealize Log Insight, follow these steps.
 
Navigate to the "Content Pack" menu in Log Insight. Select the "Import Content Pack" button. In the "Import Content Pack" menu, do the following:
 - Select the "Browse..." button and select the content pack you are trying to import
 - Select the "Install as content pack" radio button
 - Select the "Import" button
 
2. Configuration
 
The content pack requires the Log Insight agent configured using the ingestion API. To configure a Log Insight agent to forward Oracle Database events to Log Insight, follow these steps.
 
A. Listener log
Append the following to the Log Insight agent's liagent.ini configuration file and change its directory value to the path to your listener.log:
 
[filelog|ordbms_listener]
directory=/path/to/oracle/diag/tnslsnr/installation/listener/trace
include=listener.log
event_marker=^((?:Mon|Tue|Wed|Thu|Fri|Sat|Sun) (?:Jan|Feb|Mar|Apr|May|Jun|Jul|Aug|Sep|Oct|Nov|Dec) \d{1,2} \d{1,2}:\d\d:\d\d \d{4}|\d{2}-(JAN|FEB|MAR|APR|MAY|JUN|JUL|AUG|SEP|OCT|NOV|DEC)-\d{4} \d\d:\d\d:\d\d)
tags={"product":"ora_db","product_subtype":"listener"}
 
B. Alert logs
For each database instance you will monitor on this server, append the following to the Log Insight agent's liagent.ini configuration file and change each section title's SID and directory value to that of each instance being monitored:
 
[filelog|ordbms_SID]
directory=/path/to/oracle/diag/rdbms/database/SID/trace
include=alert_*.log
event_marker=^(?:Mon|Tue|Wed|Thu|Fri|Sat|Sun) (?:Jan|Feb|Mar|Apr|May|Jun|Jul|Aug|Sep|Oct|Nov|Dec) \d{1,2} \d{1,2}:\d\d:\d\d \d{4}
tags={"product":"ora_db","product_subtype":"alert"}
 
C. Restart the VMware vRealize Log Insight Agent service to make it start using its updated configuration file.
name: Oracle - Database
author: Blue Medora

info:
The Palo Alto Networks PAN-OS content pack provides you with powerful insight into your PAN-OS logs (currently SYSTEM, CONFIG and THREAT; TRAFFIC and HIP-MATCH will be added in a later version of the content pack).
 
Log Field Definitions
 
Each standard field for each of the log types is defined, allowing you to easily perform queries using any of the fields.
 
Field names are in the format:
 
pan_{log,system,config,threat}_fieldname
 
pan_log_fieldname is used for the fixed location fields that are common to all the log types, and includes: receive_time, serial, type, subtype and time_generated.
 
pan_{system,config,threat}_fieldname is used for a field specific to the SYSTEM, CONFIG and THREAT logs.
 
Descriptions for each field can be found "Syslog Field Descriptions" section in the PAN-OS Administrator's Guide:

https://paloaltonetworks.com/documentation/61/pan-os/pan-os/section_6/chapter_38.html

Configuring PAN-OS to Forward Logs to Log Insight

You will need to configure each firewall to forward its logs to Log Insight for analysis, or alternatively forward logs to Panorama and then forward to Log Insight.
 
To configure log forwarding to external hosts refer to the "Forward Logs to External Services" section in the PAN-OS Administrator's Guide:

https://www.paloaltonetworks.com/documentation/61/pan-os/pan-os/section_6/chapter_20.html
name: Palo Alto Networks - PAN-OS
author: Palo Alto Networks, Inc.

NSX-vSphere Content Pack provides powerful filtering, logging visualization and alerting of NSX for vSphere real-time operational activities.  This enables users to effectively monitor NSX-vSphere production installations using intuitive Log Insight UI dashboard widgets with just a couple clicks.

Highlights:

Easy, at a glance, views of an entire NSX-vSphere environment and components.  Users will know at a glance whether there is a problem with a NSX-vSphere environment by simply looking at the Overview dashboard.

The Content Pack highlights many areas of a NSX-vSphere environment including:
    Common Installation / Configuration issues - exposes several targeted problem log patterns with actionable remediations

    Logical Router - exposes system logs, audit logs and several targeted problem log patterns with actionable remediations
    Distributed Firewall - contains several different dashboards to exposes firewall traffic by total aggregate traffic, hypervisors and rule Ids
    Edge Services - separates logs for Edge appliance, health check, communication agent, high availability, load balancer, firewall and Ipsec VPN services
    Edge Firewall - contains several widgets for monitoring firewall traffic

Where to begin:

info:
VMware Site Recovery Manager is a business continuity and disaster recovery solution that helps you to plan, test, and run the recovery of virtual machines between a protected vCenter Server site and a recovery vCenter Server site.

Site Recovery Manager orchestrates the recovery process with the replication mechanisms, to minimize data loss and system down time.
  • At the protected site, Site Recovery Manager shuts down virtual machines cleanly and synchronizes storage, if the protected site is still running.
  • Site Recovery Manager powers on the replicated virtual machines at the recovery site according to a recovery plan.

A recovery plan specifies the order in which virtual machines start up on the recovery site. A recovery plan specifies network parameters, such as IP addresses, and can contain user-specified scripts that Site Recovery Manager can run to perform custom recovery actions on virtual machines.

This content pack a deeper look into SRM and SRA logs for analysis and troubleshooting.

info:
VMware vRealize Operations Manager content pack is provided to present log data in a more meaningful way and to analyze all the logs redirected from a vRealize Operations Manager instance(s). The content pack contains various dashboards, queries and alerts to provide better diagnostics and troubleshooting capabilities to the vRealize Operations Manager administrator. The content pack provides: 

Proactive monitoring and alert notifications of the vRealize Operations clusters
Specific alerts focused on important events that indicate problems can be enabled to get the alerts in vRops as well as for sending emails to the administrator(s).

Cluster-role specific breakdown of vRealize Operations events
The dashboards are grouped based on the cluster role of the vRops nodes/slices like Master, Data, Replica and Remote Collector to provide better manageability.

 Highlights
The VMware vRealize Operations Manager (vRops) content pack provides a consolidated summary of log events across all vRops components of the environment including the vRops Telemetry, vRops cassandra Components,vRops casa Components . This includes updates to vRops queries to account for new log format introduced in 6.1+. This version of the content pack is designed specifically for vRops 6.1 or above. It is also compatible with vRops 6.0.x versions.
    - Proactive monitoring of vRops environment node wise
    - Component-specific breakdown of vRops events node wise
    - Troubleshooting and root-cause analysis

Content Pack Components
The vRealize Operation Manager content pack comprises of the following components:
- 19 Dashboard Groups
- 109 Dashboard Widgets
- 20 Queries
- 9 Alerts
- 45 Extracted Fields

 Compatibility
The vRealize Operations Manager content pack requires vRealize Log Insight version 2.5+ and vRealize Operations Manager version 6.x+.

Cluster - Cassandra Overview, Cluster - Telemetry Overview dashboards and alerts are only for version 6.1+


IMPORTANT:The Log Insight agent uses the cfapi and specific tags are required for this content pack to work. For directions on proper agent configuration see the Setup Instructions of vRops CP.

info:
NOTE: This content pack is for informational purposes only. If you would like to monitor vCenter server and/or ESXi logs then please upgrade theLog Insight appliance to get the latest version of the content pack.

The vSphere content pack provides powerful insight into your vCenter Server and ESXi logs, allowing you to make informed and proactive decisions within your environment. Be sure to checkout the other VMware content packs that may be applicable to your Software Defined Data Center including:
  • VMware - NSX-vSphere
  • VMware - VSAN
Also, please install the applicable operating system content packs in order to have full visibility into all available events:
  • ESXi: Linux
  • vCenter Server: Microsoft - Windows
  • vCenter Server Appliance (VCSA): Linux

IMPORTANT: To fully leverage the power of this content pack both vSphere integration and vRealize Operations integration is required. In addition, the Log Insight agent must be installed on all vCenter Server instances and agent groups, available in this content pack, need to be enabled.

This content pack enables:

Proactive monitoring of your vSphere environment
  • Quickly identify issues: The General - Problems dashboard gives you a single pane of glass to find problems in your vSphere environment while the General - Performance dashboard does the same to isolate performance issues.
  • Drill down to determine the root cause: Dashboard filters make it easy to see logs from specific parts of your vSphere environment.
  • Easily consume data: Powerful and dynamic visualizations make it possible to detect anomalies, perform trending analysis, and pinpoint specific issues through targeted queries.
  • Alerts: Know what to monitor in your vSphere logs and get notified when such events are detected.

Track changes and isolate security threats
  • Configuration management: Track user-initiated changes and automated vSphere actions through the vCenter Server - Tasks dashboard.
  • Environmental changes: Get a complete picture from the General - Auditing dashboard or see more specific information like what VMs are being moved through DRS and HA actions.
  • Security: The General - Security dashboard allows you to find who is logging into vSphere devices from which locations and through what means.

Additional information and context
  • Query notes: Each dashboard widget includes information about the widget with links to documentation, knowledge base articles, and any other information making it possible to understand the data presented.
  • Inventory: The General - Inventory dashboard quantifies results seen through vSphere logs making it simple to ensure complete environment monitoring.
